cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI

This paper deals with the security problem of overprivilege in Android apps and proposes an approach to identify the minimum permissions required by an app. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). 

However, the paper also involves the use of static analysis and collaborative filtering, which are techniques commonly used in software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed approach using experiments, which could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) or social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, the other likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.SI, in descending order of likelihood.
